        "id": 258214,
        "name": "Tam",
        "username": "Tamnon",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/90ced4/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-01-04T04:39:03.618Z",
        "cooked": "<p>When voice messaging it would be nice to be able to pause the voice message I am currently making and be able to resume making the voice message without having to send one message and create a new one. Though I will say, I absolutely LOVE that I can minimize the conversation while listening to a voice message so I can view other things on my phone while still hearing the message.</p>\n<p>Also, I have found that when my proximity sensor gets covered, my screen goes black and stops any voice message Iâ€™m listening to. It wonâ€™t pause the message Iâ€™m listening to, so when I click to play the message I have to try and find where I left off in the voice message, which is frustrating. This also makes it so when I start listening to the message again, the volume is lowered significantly and I have to back out of the conversation, then go back in the conversation, click on the voice message I was listening to again, and then find where I left off in the message. Again, very frustrating.</p>\n<p>Another thing is, when initially trying to start a voice message, the act of having to hold down the mic and flick it upwards to be hands free is frustrating. It would be more user friendly to have just a one push mic button that stays on without having to hold it down throughout the entire time making the voice message or holding down and flicking upwards to lock it so it can be hands free.</p>\n<p>I do hope you take this feedback into consideration, as I know myself and my friends and family have these same concerns. And maybe others on your app do too.</p>",
